7. Nd5 { Avoids the knight trade. White wants to go either Nh4 or Ne3. } 7...
c6
{ We close the long diagonal and chase the knight away before White goes Nh4. }
8. Ne3 { Attacking our bishop. } 8... Be6
{ The bishop is active here, and we leave the d7-square for the knight. } 9.
O-O O-O 10. Qc2
{ Hitting the e4-knight and forcing us to make a decision about it. } 10... f5
{ We support the knight this way so we can play ...Nd7 and have the f7-square for the bishop.   A solid alternative is  10...d5  , reaching a rather symmetrical position. }
11. b3 { Going for Bb2 to finish development. } 11... Nd7
{ Finishing development as well. } 12. Bb2 Ndf6
{ We reached a playable Dutch-type position. We have a strong knight on e4 and ...a5 should be a useful move. Giri played this in Titled Tuesday and won his game. }
