{ It's always good to bring a new piece into play with tempo. } 12. Be2 Qxf6
{ We need to recover some material and avoid the queen trade. } 13. O-O Nf8
{ A good regrouping move − its main point is to play ...Bf5 or ...Bd7-c6 followed by ...Rad8. The position is very unusual, our pieces will be active while White has problems with development. We also intend to attack the king with ...g5. }
