{ This rare sideline will certainly surprise your opponent. The point is to protect e5 with the knight and try to push ...d5 on the next move. If White prevents this, we can switch to the ...g6 and ...Bg7 setup.   We recommend  4...Nbd7  over  4...d5  or  4...Nc6  in order to play some fresh positions, where we can even fight for a win with Black. }
