{ Forced. } 13. cxd3 { 13.Rxe4  Nxc1  is just equal. } 13... Nd6
{ Again, the only move −the knight needs to cover the king. } 14. Nxe5
{ A logical move, keeping the e-file open and threatening Ng6+. } 14... Kd8
{ The most precise reply, preparing ...f6 or ...Be6. } 15. Ba3
{ Threatening Bxd6 and Nxf7+. } 15... Be6
{ We're just in time to defend the f7-pawn. We will follow up with ...Re8 and then ...f6. The position is even. }
