{ We're activating the bishop. The knight will go to d6 or c7. } 14. axb7
{ White creates the c6-weakness. } 14... Nxb7
{ Giving ourselves the option of ...c5, and it's nice that  15.Nxc6  doesn't work because of  15...Qb6+  . We have good perspectives because of our mobile center.   A sample line goes  15.Be3  Nc7  @@StartBracket@@we're not afraid of  16.Nxc6?  because of  16...Qe8!  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pnn3pp/2p2b2/3p4/3N4/2N1BP2/1PP1B1PP/R2Q1RK1 w - - 2 16@@EndFEN@@  16.Bd2  Qd6  .  Black is comfortable, given the multiple options at our disposal: ...Be5, ...Bd7, ...a5, etc. }
