2. d4 { White takes control of the whole center. } 2... Nf6
{ We're attacking the e4-pawn, forcing White to make a decision. } 3. Nc3
{ The most popular move by far. } 3... e5
{ The Philidor Defense. With our last move, we gain a foothold in the center. }
4. Nf3 { The main move. } 4... Nbd7 { We're defending the e5-pawn. } 5. Be3
{ White has two possible plans: to go h3 and g4 with a kingside attack, or h3, Bd3, O-O with a solid setup. }
5... Be7
{ We're continuing development. There is not much benefit in going ...Ng4, because White can play Bd2. The immediate  5...c6  is also possible. }
6. h3 { Making sure ...Ng4 is never there and also preparing g4. } 6... c6
{ Preparing ...b5.  7.Qd2  was played sometimes, but it allows  7...b5  with good play for Black. }
7. g4 { White continues pushing on the kingside. } 7... h6
{ This is how we always react. } 8. a4
{ Stopping ...b5.  8.Rg1  transposes to the 5.h3 variation. } 8... Qa5
