{ We're preparing ...d5. We want to open the position even further as we have a lead in development, and White played f3. }
10. O-O { Finally. } 10... d5 { Breaking open the center right away. } 11. exd5
cxd5
{ We have an isolated pawn, but White played f3 and weakened their position. Here, ...a6 and ...Re8 are useful moves, as in the long term, we want to play ...Qc7 and ...Bd6. The position is about equal. }
