Nxa8 { The only way to justify the sacrifice on f7. } 10... Qxg2
{ Now the white king will be weak. } 11. Rf1 { Forced. } 11... exd4
{ We want to follow up with ...Ne5. } 12. Qxd4 Ne5
{ Stopping Qc4+ and threatening ...Nf3+. } 13. f3
{ The only defense.  13.f4  just loses to  13...Nfg4  followed by ...Bh4+. }
13... Nh5 { With the strong threat of ...Bh4+. } 14. Rf2 { Again forced. }
14... Bh4 15. Ke2 { Unpinning the rook. } 15... Qg6
{ Our idea is to play ...h6, ...Kh7, and ...Rf8, and there is little White can do about it despite the extra material. Black is winning here.   It's important not to take  15...Bxf2  immediately so that after  16.Qxf2  Qh3  , White doesn't have  17.Nd5  threatening Ne7+. }
