9... exf4 { Forced. } 10. Ne6 Qg8 { We don't want Nxc7 to come with tempo. }
11. Nd5
{ The best move. After  11.Nxf4+  Kf7  , the king gets to safety, or @@StartFEN@@r1b3qr/pppnb1pp/4Nnk1/8/4Pp2/2N5/PPP3PP/R1BQK2R w KQ - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Nxc7  Ne5!  is very good for Black,  as ...Bg4 is next.  12.Nxa8  Bg4  13.Qd4  Nc6!  and we take on a8 afterwards. }
11... Bd6 { Now we're ready to take on e6. } 12. Nexc7 { The only move. } 12...
Bxc7
{ We don't mind giving up the queen because we get many pieces in return. } 13.
Ne7+ { This is the point, White takes the queen. } 13... Kf7 14. Nxg8 Rxg8
{ The material is unbalanced − 3 pieces vs. queen and pawn. However, once we get a good piece coordination, Black will get a big advantage. The black king is still exposed to some checks for now, but White is lacking attacking pieces. }
