{ We've seen this before. We have good control over the d5-square because of the knight on b4, and also the c2-pawn can be hanging sometimes. The position is about equal.   A sample line goes  14.Qe2  Bxc4  15.Qxc4  Nxc2  16.Rad1  Qb6  , when White has compensation for the pawn but no more than that. }
