12... Ne8
{ We usually don't like to move the pieces backwards, but here this regrouping is justified as we defend d6. We have ideas to play ...Qb6 or ...f5 if White removes the bishop from c4. }
13. b3
{ White consolidates the queenside.  13.Nd2  can be met with  13...Qb6  . }
13... Bxc4 { It is a good time to trade the bishops. } 14. Qxc4 Qb6
{ We have ideas such as ...Rd8 or ...Qb4. After ...Rd8, we can bring the knight into play with ...Nf6. Also, if we trade the queen, ...f5 can be a good idea. White has no clear way to open up the position. }
