[Result "*"]

1. e4
{ White is going for an open game, taking control of the center right away. }
1... d6 { We're preparing ...Nf6 without allowing the e-pawn to move forward. }
2. d4 { White takes control of the whole center. } 2... Nf6
{ We're attacking the e4-pawn, forcing White to make a decision. } 3. Nc3
{ The most popular move by far. } 3... e5
{ The Philidor Defense. With our last move, we gain a foothold in the center. }
4. Nf3 { The main move. } 4... Nbd7 { We're defending the e5-pawn. } 5. Bc4
{ The most played move. White is already threatening Ng5. } 5... Be7
{ Now we can parry Ng5 with ...O-O. } 6. O-O O-O 7. a4
{ A good prophylactic move. White can play a5 to gain some more space on the queenside, and also after ...c6, there is no ...b5. }
7... c6
{ This is the alternative recommendation against the main line Philidor. We still want to take on d4, but not immediately. We will also prepare it by playing ...a5 and securing the c5-square for the knight. }
8. Qe2
{ The idea is to play Rd1 and put pressure on the d-file, but this is just not very good. }
8... exd4
{ It's important to open the e-file, as the white queen is misplaced. } 9. Nxd4
Re8 { Preparing ...Bf8 and ...d5. } 10. Ba2
{ A useful move, the bishop is not exposed on a2. If White goes  10.Be3  or  10.Bf4  , we just go  10...Bf8  and Black is already preferable. }
10... Bf8
{ With the idea ...d5 or ...Nc5. Obviously, the queen is misplaced on e2. } 11.
f3 { Consolidating the e4-pawn, and not being afraid of ...d5. } 11... d5
{ Of course, we go for this. } 12. Qf2
{ Avoiding the pin and claiming that if we take on e4, there will be pressure on the f-file. }
12... dxe4
{ Probably the easiest solution. We're clarifying the situation in the center. }
13. Nxe4 { It makes sense to trade a knight to get to the f7-pawn. } 13... Nxe4
14. fxe4 Nf6 { The only way to defend f7. } 15. Bg5 { Pinning the knight. }
15... Rxe4
{ Just grabbing the pawn. The position will most likely simplify to an equal endgame. A sample line is  16.Bxf6  Qxf6  17.Bxf7+  Kh8  18.Qxf6  gxf6  19.c3  Bc5  .   The immediate  15...Bc5  is also possible. }
