{ It makes sense to take advantage of the white bishop being on d2. } 12. Nxc6
{ White takes a pawn. } 12... bxc6 13. hxg4 Be5
{ An important move, threatening ...Qh4. We want to weaken White's position before taking on c3 and getting back the pawn. White should play g5 or g3 to parry ...Qh4, but then we take ...Bxc3 followed by ...Nxe4. }
