{ This is the alternative recommendation against the main line Philidor. We still want to take on d4, but not immediately. We will also prepare it by playing ...a5 and securing the c5-square for the knight. }
8. Re1 { This is the main move. } 8... a5
{ We make sure that White never has b4 after we take on d4 and play ...Nc5. }
9. b3 { The idea is to fianchetto Bb2 or even go Ba3. } 9... exd4
{ The good thing about this line is that the idea is always the same − clearing the center and then going ...Ne5 or ...Nc5. }
10. Qxd4 { One of the possible captures. } 10... Ne5
{ Not really a pawn sacrifice, as it's not good for White to take the pawn. The usual plan with  10...Nc5  is not good here because of  11.Ba3!  Be6  12.Bxc5  . }
11. Nxe5 { Let's see what happens if White tries to take the pawn. } 11... dxe5
12. Qxe5 { After  12.Qxd8  or  12.Qe3  , Black is completely fine. } 12... Ng4
{ After this move, White doesn't have a good square for the queen. } 13. Qf4
{ The only way.  13.Qg3?  Bh4  is not recommended. } 13... Bd6
{ Again, attacking the queen since it has no good squares. } 14. e5 { Forced. }
14... Nxe5
{ We took back the pawn with a promising position as  15.Rxe5  loses to  15...Qc7! }
