12... fxe6 13. e5
{ The only attempt for an advantage, as after  13.Be3  d5  , Black is already preferable. }
13... dxe5 14. Qxd8 { Preparing Rxe5 next. } 14... Raxd8 15. Rxe5 Nd5
{ Black has active pieces, and it's not easy for White to attack the e6-pawn. In practice, Black's position is already preferable. }
