14. exd6 { Forced. } 14... Rxf4 15. dxe7 Qxe7 16. Qe2
{ Defending the bishop and attacking on e6. } 16... Raf8
{ Of course, we put the rook on the open file. If White takes on e6, the f2-pawn will be hanging in the end. }
17. f3 { Defending the pawn but creating weaknesses on the dark squares. }
17... R8f6
{ Defending the e6-pawn and activating the rook. We think Black has a good position because of the active pieces. Normally we'd stop the analysis here, but we'll continue just because it was given in Wesley So's Chessable course 1.e4 − Part 1. }
18. b3 { Securing the a4-pawn. } 18... Nb6
{ Activating the knight and hitting the c4-bishop. } 19. Bd3 Nd5
