{ The only try for an advantage. } 20... Nxe4 21. Bxe4 Nc3
{ Not the only move, but the most forcing one. Wesley So only mentions  21...Qc7  in this course. }
22. Qc4 { Not allowing ...Qc5+. } 22... Nxe4
{ We want to simplify the position. } 23. Rxe4 Qd6
{ Activating the queen as well, and creating the threat of ...Rxf3. We only have one weakness − the e6-pawn, which can be easily defended and it's compensated by the active pieces. The position is equal. }
