{ It looks very natural to try to save the bishop and not double the pawns. }
13... Ne6
{ This looks more forcing, as we take the bishop pair.  13...Be6  is also fine. }
14. Bxe6 fxe6
{ The more precise recapture. We attack the f4-bishop and we want to go ...e5 and ...Be6 next. }
