f4
{ The critical continuation. White is intending to put a lot of pressure on the center with f4 and Nf3. }
6... Ngf6
{ We need to develop the knight quickly. If we manage to stabilize the position, we'll have a great game, but for now, we need to be precise; every tempo counts. }
7. fxe5 { White is forcing our knight to e5 to attack it with Bf4 and O-O-O. }
7... Nxe5 8. Bf4 { Hitting the knight and preparing O-O-O. } 8... Bd6
{ We're finishing development. } 9. Nb5
{ Immediately putting pressure on the d6-bishop.  9.O-O-O  is slower, as it allows us to play  9...Bd7  10.Bg2  Kc8  , when we get out of the pin. After  11.Nf3  Re8  , we have everything defended, and we keep a better structure. }
9... Bd7 { Simply continuing our plan. } 10. Nxd6
{ White gets the bishop pair. } 10... cxd6
{ Now the e5-knight is well protected. } 11. Nf3
{ Trying to challenge the e5-knight. } 11... Re8
{ The rook will be useful on the e-file. We managed to stabilize the position and coordinate our pieces. We will continue with ...Kc7 and ...Bc6 with a solid position. }
