7. e4 e5 8. h3 { White wants to go Be3 without allowing ...Ng4. } 8... c6
{ We want to seize space with ...b5. } 9. Be3
{ White continues their plan. The bishop is well placed on e3. } 9... b5
{ It's important to remember this idea. If White doesn't go a4, we just grab space on the queenside. Black's position is already preferable.   A sample line is  10.dxe5  dxe5  11.Qd6  Bb7  12.Rfd1  Re8  . White's active moves led nowhere. }
