{ This was also possible to reach via @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp1ppbp/3p1np1/8/3P4/5NP1/PPP1PPBP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 2 5@@EndFEN@@  5.b3  b5  .  White wants to go for a double fianchetto after Bb2.   6.a4  a5  would most likely transpose to @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/ppp1ppbp/3p1np1/8/3P4/5NP1/PPP1PPBP/RNBQ1RK1 w - - 4 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Re1  or  6.Nc3  , as  we'll play ...Nbd7 and ...e5, while White will play Nc3 and e4. }
