Rb8
{ This is a prophylactic move, as we're stopping White's normal development with Qc2 and Rad1.   After  13.Qc2  , now we can take  13...Nxe4  14.Bxe4  Bxd4  and the bishop  on b7 is defended. Our next move is ...Nc5, and we'll probably force White to play f3, creating weaknesses.   It was premature to play  12...Nc5  because of  13.Qc2!  and the tactics to  take on e4 don't work. }
