10... Bg7 11. Bg2 O-O
{ Finally, we completed our development, and we can start considering ideas like ...Nd7-c5, targeting b3. }
12. Nf3 Nd7 { ...Nc5 is a real threat. } 13. Nd5
{ White is trying to trade the bishops. The knight looks great on d5, but it allows ...Ra2. }
13... Ra2 { Obviously, we go for this. The pin is very annoying. } 14. Nc3
{ This is forced, as White has to get the knight back. } 14... Rxb2
{ We can repeat the moves if we want with  13...Ra8  , or play on with this interesting exchange sac. }
15. Qxb2 Nc5
{ Black has the initiative and very nice compensation for the exchange. We have firm control over the long diagonal, the b3-pawn is weak, and we can easily activate our pieces by ...Bf5 and ...Re8. }
