[Round "?"]
[White "13) English Rat Defense 1.d4 d6 2.c4 e5"]
[Black "English Rat Defense 1.d4 d6 2.c4 e5 3.Nf3 #6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4
{ The second-most played move in practice. It's considered more solid than  1.e4  , when White usually aims for a long-term small edge from the opening. }
1... d6
{ Our usual reply, preparing ...e5 and waiting for White to show their plans. }
2. c4
{ White's idea is to play Nc3 and e4, and delay the development of the knight to f3. We are already happy to see this because it allows us to play ...e5. }
2... e5
{ Of course, we go for this. The whole point of ...d6 is to go ...e5 whenever possible and control the center. }
3. Nf3
{ The main move, immediately putting pressure on e5. This is more likely what stronger players will do. }
3... e4
{ We accept the challenge and chase away the knight; it would have been too passive to defend the e5-pawn. }
4. Ng5
{ The most played continuation, trying to keep the knight active. However, it has its drawbacks, as we'll be able to gain some tempi with ...Be7 or ...h6, attacking the knight. }
4... f5
{ We support the e4-pawn.  4...Nf6  is not so good because White can attack  the e4-pawn with  5.Nc3  Qe7  6.Qc2  . }
5. g3
{ The second most played move, although objectively it's not great. White's idea could be h4, when the pawn is defended, or Bg2 and f3 to break the center. }
5... h6 { Here, it's good to drive the white knight back. } 6. Nh3 g5
{ The point of the previous move. The knight is on the rim and the plan with Ng1 and h4 is ineffective. }
7. Nc3
{ White is developing for now and will see about the h3-knight later. There are two plans − to go Ng1 and h4 or to play Bg2 and f3. }
7... Bg7 { Our plan remains the same − we intend to meet Ng1 with ...c5. } 8.
Bg2 { With the idea to castle and go f3. } 8... c6
{ A new move, we're ready to reinforce the center with ...d5.   If White goes  9.d5  , we can take  9...Bxc3+  10.bxc3  c5  with a strategically great position.   8...Nf6  or  8...Nc6  is also good. }
9. f3 { White undermines the center. } 9... d5 { We go for this as planned. }
10. O-O Nf6
{ Intending to castle. Black has a nice center and a slightly better position.   If  11.fxe4  , it's better to take back with the d-pawn  11...dxe4  so that d5 is not a weakness anymore and we keep the f-file closed.   And if  11.Qb3  , then  11...Qb6  is the most precise. }
