9... O-O
{ We first bring the king to safety, and then we can follow with ...Nc7-e6. }
10. d5
{ White is trying to stop us from playing ...d5. However, that gives up two important squares − e5 and c5. }
10... Ng4
{ This is the right reaction. For the moment, we attack the h4-pawn. We want to activate the bishop with ...Bf6, and then we have ideas of ...Bxc3 to double the pawns or ...Be5. }
