10. h5
{ Quite a rare move, although the most challenging one. White seizes more space, and the pawn is well-defended on h5. Also, if we go ...Kh8 there could be Ng6+ ideas in some lines. }
10... Rf7
{ A prophylactic move, covering the a2-g8 diagonal in advance. After this ...d5 is on our agenda again. }
11. Bd2
{ This was tried in correspondence games. White is getting ready if we play ...d5. Both  11.Be2  or  11.b3  can be met with  11...d5  , with a solid center for Black. }
11... Nc7 { Intending ...Ne6 or ...d5. } 12. d5
{ Now, this is better, as our knight cannot go to c5 in one move. } 12... Ng4
{ The typical reaction to d5, intending ...Ne5. } 13. Be2 Ne5
{ Both sides have their plusses and minuses in this position. It remains a complicated struggle. Our next moves are ...Bd7 and ...Bf6. }
