[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14) English Opening 1.c4 d6 − Without 2.d4"]
[Black "English Opening 1.c4 d6 2.e4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4
{ The English Opening. This move fights for the center, and also allows White more flexible setups. }
1... d6 { We're not impressed. We go  1...d6  against everything. } 2. e4
{ White is seizing more space in the center and tries to avoid the lines after  2.d4  e5  .  White can prepare d4 in better conditions, or just play d3. }
2... e5
{ We get a foothold in the center, and our idea is to continue with ...f5, ...Nf6. }
3. Nf3
{ With the idea to push d4. However, this is a known inaccuracy for White. }
3... c5
{ The right moment to block the center, as we'll be able to develop with ...Nc6, ...g6, ...Bg7, ...Nge7 and prepare ...f5. White cannot do the same because of the knight on f3. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14) English Opening 1.c4 d6 − Without 2.d4"]
[Black "English Opening 1.c4 d6 2.e4 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4
{ The English Opening. This move fights for the center, and also allows White more flexible setups. }
1... d6 { We're not impressed. We go  1...d6  against everything. } 2. e4
{ White is seizing more space in the center and tries to avoid the lines after  2.d4  e5  .  White can prepare d4 in better conditions, or just play d3. }
2... e5
{ We get a foothold in the center, and our idea is to continue with ...f5, ...Nf6. }
3. Nc3 { White continues to develop normally. } 3... f5
{ Challenging White's center. This is good because we break the symmetry and get some counterplay.  3...c5  is also possible but too drawish for our taste. }
4. exf5
{ White is trying to open up the center quickly with a quick d4, without including g3 and Bg2. }
4... Bxf5 5. Nge2
{ Preparing both d4 and Ng3. If  5.Nf3  ,  with the idea to push d4, there is  5...c5  blocking the center, and the white knight is slightly misplaced  on f3. }
5... Bd3
{ We take advantage of the awkward position of the knight on e2, and we stop d4. Normally, it's not good to move the same piece twice in the opening, but with this, we stop White's ideas. }
6. Ng3 { White needs to untangle. } 6... Bxf1 7. Nxf1
{ The only move to keep castle an option. } 7... Nc6
{ We just stop d4. We're going to develop with ...Nf6, ...Be7, and ...O-O with a good position. }
*

