4... g6
{ We intend to fianchetto to counter White's bishop on b2 when the position opens up. }
5. c4 { White prepares d4 and takes away the option of ...d5. } 5... Bg7 6. d4
{ Just as planned. } 6... e4 { The usual reaction. } 7. Nfd2 c5
{ Now that White took away our option to go ...d5, we switch to the plan to undermine the center with ...c5. This works because we have the bishop on g7. Black enjoys a nice position because of the misplaced knight on d2. Our plan is to make simple developing moves like ...O-O, ...Nc6, ...Bf5, ...h5, ...Re8, and so on. }
